        <h2 id="carrot-cake">Carrot Cake</h2>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/87/Rueblitorte.jpg/220px-Rueblitorte.jpg" alt="A delicious carrot cake">
        <h4>What you'll need</h4>
        <table border>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                <th><strong>Ingredients </strong></th>
                <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td> 1/2 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Grated carrots</td>
                    <td>3</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Eggs</td>
                    <td>4</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Fluor</td>
                    <td>2 and 1/2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Baking Powder</td>
                    <td>1 spoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4>How you can make it in 5 steps</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>In a blender, add the carrots, eggs and oil, then blend.</li>
            <li>Add sugar and blend again for 5 minutes</li>
            <li>In a bowl or in a a stand mixer, add Fluor and beat again</li>
            <li>Add the baking powder and mix slowly with a spoon</li>
            <li>Bake in an oven preheated to 180°C for approximately 40 minutes.</li>
        </ol>
     <h2 id="chicken-straganoff">Chicken Stroganoff</h2>
     <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Beef_Stroganoff-02_cropped.jpg/800px-Beef_Stroganoff-02_cropped.jpg" alt="A Delicious Stroganoff" width="230">
      <h4>What you'll need</h4>
        <table border>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                <th><strong>Ingredients </strong></th>
                <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Chicken Breast Cut Into Cubes</td>
                    <td>500 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Chopped Onion</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Minced Garlic Clove</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>To taste</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Chili</td>
                    <td>To taste</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Butter</td>
                    <td>1 Spoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Mayo</td>
                    <td>2 Spoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Mustard</td>
                    <td>1 Spoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Ketchup</td>
                    <td>1/2 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Mushrooms</td>
                    <td>1 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Milk Cream</td>
                    <td>1 Box</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Potato Sticks</td>
                    <td>To taste</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4>How you can make it in 8 steps</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Season the cubed chicken with salt, pepper and mayonnaise.</li>
            <li>In a large skillet melt the butter.</li>
            <li>Fry the onion and garlic.</li>
            <li>Add the seasoned chicken and let it brown.</li>
            <li>Add the mushrooms, mustard and then the ketchup.</li>
            <li>Add the cream and mix well.</li>
            <li>Make salt and pepper corrections if necessary.</li>
            <li>Serve with white rice and potatoes chips</li>
        </ol>
        <h2 id="lasagna">Lasagna</h2>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Lasagna_%281%29.jpg/185px-Lasagna_%281%29.jpg" alt="A Delicios Lasagna">
        <h4>What you'll need</h4>
        <table border>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                <th><strong>Ingredients </strong></th>
                <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Lasagna Noodles</td>
                    <td>500 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Ground beef</td>
                    <td>500 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Milk Cream</td>
                    <td>2 Boxes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Butter</td>
                    <td>3 Spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Fluor</td>
                    <td>3 Spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Ham</td>
                    <td>500 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Mozzarella</td>
                    <td>500 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>To Taste</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>2 Cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Grated Onion</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>2 Spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Tomato Sauce</td>
                    <td>1 Box</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Crushed Garlic</td>
                    <td>3 Teeth</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Grated Cheese</td>
                    <td>1 Pack</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4>How you can make it in 12 steps</h4>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>To Lasagna:</strong> </li>
            <li>Cook the pasta according to the manufacturer's instructions, pour it into a refractory with ice water so it doesn't stick and set aside. </li>
            <li><strong>To Bolognese sauce: </strong></li>
            <li>Saute the garlic, onion, ground beef, tomato sauce, cook for 3 minutes and set aside. </li>
            <li><strong>To White Sauce: </strong></li>
            <li>Melt the margarine, add the 3 tablespoons of wheat flour and stir. </li>
            <li>Slowly pour in the milk and keep stirring. </li>
            <li>Finally, add the cream, stir for 1 minute and turn off the heat. </li>
            <li><strong>To Assembly: </strong> </li>
            <li>Pour a part of the bolognese sauce in a refractory, half of the pasta, half of the ham, half of the mozzarella, all the white sauce and the rest of the pasta. </li>
            <li>Repeat layers to the edge of the container. </li>
            <li>Finish with the grated cheese and take it to the high oven (220°C), preheated, for about 20 minutes. </li>
        </ol>
     <h2 id="ninho">Ninho Ice Cream</h2>
     <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f3/Vanilla_Ice_Cream_Cone_at_Camp_Manitoulin.jpg" alt="A Delicious Ninho Ice Cream" width="130">
     <h4>What you'll need</h4>
        <table border>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                <th><strong>Ingredients </strong></th>
                <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Condensed Milk</td>
                    <td>1 Can</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Milk Cream</td>
                    <td>1 Box</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Unflavored Gelatin</td>
                    <td>1/2 Pack</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Water</td>
                    <td>1 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Nido Milk</td>
                    <td>4 Spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Chopped Chocolate(Optional)</td>
                    <td>To Taste</td>
                </tr>
                
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4>How you can make it in 4 steps</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Hydrate the gelatin with 4 tablespoons of water in the microwave for 15 seconds. </li>
            <li>Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for 3 minutes. </li>
            <li>Refrigerate for about 12 hours. </li>
            <li>Once ready, if you wish, add chopped chocolate to decorate. </li>
        </ol>
        <h2 id="french-fries">French Fries</h2>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/83/French_Fries.JPG" alt="Delicious French Fries" width="230">
        <h4>What you'll need</h4>
        <table border>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th><strong>Ingredients </strong></th>
                <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Potatoes</td>
                    <td>3</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>1 Liter</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass1">
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>To Taste</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="tclass2">
                    <td>Fluor</td>
                    <td>2 Spoons</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4>How you can make it in 5 steps</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Put the oil to heat. </li>
            <li>Meanwhile, peel the potatoes and cut them into sticks. </li>
            <li>Place the cut potatoes in a bowl and add the flour or starch; shake well so that it mixes in the potatoes. </li>
            <li>Fry them in very hot oil until golden. </li>
            <li>Place on paper towels and add salt to taste. </li>
        </ol>
